Package com.esri.mo2.map.dpy

Support for major Map components.

See:
          Description

Interface Summary
DatasetLayer A DatasetLayer is a visual representation of a particular MapDataset.
Display This class implements an off-screen rendering surface.
DisplayArea A DisplayArea is a portion of a Display corresponding with a particular area of interest (map area) that can be rendered upon.
DisplayListener An interface for objects wishing to be notified about DisplayEvents.
DisplayManager Manages the drawing of a Layerset's Layers to a particular Display.
Element A a visual object that can be displayed in a GraphicsLayer.
FeatureGraphicsLayer Manages a collection of Elements that originate from one or more SelectableLayers.
FeatureLayer A FeatureLayer implements a visual representation of a particular FeatureClass.
FeatureSelectionListener An interface for objects that request to be notified when features are selected on feature layer.
GraphicsLayer Manages a collection of graphic Elements for display in a Map.
GroupLayer A GroupLayer is an ordered collection of Layers.
Layer A Layer is a visual representation of a Dataset or a group of Datasets.
LayerExtension Defines an optional functionality that can be added to a Layer at run-time.
LayerInfo Deprecated. - the class has been deprecated, see Content API.
LayerListener An interface for objects that request to be notified about LayerEvents.
Layerset A LayerSet is a "top-level" GroupLayer.
LayerSource Deprecated. - the interface has been deprecated, see Content API.
LayerVisitor You can traverse a GroupLayer tree by providing an implementation of LayerVisitor and calling a GroupLayer's traverse method.
MapFilter A MapFilter is a kind of SpatialFilter that is specific to a Map Display.
OSBFactory Creates an off-screen buffer (OSB) image, that is, an image that can have a graphics context (Graphics).
SelectableLayer An abstract Map Layer that supports a SelectionSet.
WorkspaceLayerSource Deprecated. - the interface has been deprecated, see Content API.
 

Class Summary
BaseDatasetLayer A standard implementation of DatasetLayer.
BaseDisplay This class is the standard implementation of Display.
BaseDisplayManager This class is the implementation of a Map DisplayManager.
BaseElement A BaseElement is an abstract Element class that provides support for Object ID.
BaseFeatureElement This object represents a GraphicsLayer Element that wraps a Feature together with appropriate Renderers.
BaseFeatureGraphicsLayer A helper class for the FeatureGraphicsLayer object.
BaseFeatureLayer A standard implementation of the FeatureLayer object.
BaseGraphicsLayer A helper class for the GraphicsLayer object.
BaseGroupLayer A standard implementation of GroupLayer.
BaseLabelElement a BaseLabelElement is a GraphicsLayer Element that wraps labelling details supplied by a LabelEngine.
BaseLayer This class is a standard implementation of the Layer object.
BaseLayerExtension This helper class provides infrastructure for accessing the Layer that a LayerExtension is added to.
BaseLayerInfo Deprecated. - the interface has been deprecated, see Content API.
BaseLayerset This is the standard implementation of Layerset.
BaseLayerSource Deprecated. - the class has been deprecated, see Content API.
BaseMapFilter A standard implementation of a MapFilter.
BaseRectangleElement A BaseRectangleElement is a GraphicsLayer Element that shows a Rectangle.
BaseWorkspaceLayerSource Deprecated. - the class has been deprecated, see Content API.
DisplayAdapter This class implements a simple adapter for DisplayListeners.
DisplayEvent This event is sent to a DisplayListener from a DisplayManager's map drawing thread when it wants to signal one of the following events: the drawing thread starts drawing on a particular DisplayArea the drawing thread finishes drawing on a DisplayArea the Display's extent has changed You can cancel rendering threads, by invoking the Map's cancel() method
FeatureSelectionAdapter A simple adapter for FeatureSelectionListener.
FeatureSelectionEvent This event is sent to a FeatureSelectionListener whenever features are added or cleared from a feature layer.
ImageElement An implementation of the image elements (typically added to a graphics layer)
ImagePainter Utility class for managing image draws.
LayerAdapter A simple adapter for LayerListeners.
LayerCapabilities Defines the capabilities for Layers.
LayerEvent Sent to a LayerListener whenever a Layer is either added-to, moved-within, or removed-from a Map.
SerializableElement This class is only intended to be used internally.
 

Exception Summary
LayerIndexException Thrown whenever a LayerCollection method detects that a Layer Index parameter is outside the bounds of the collection.
LayerNotFoundException Thrown whenever a LayerCollection method detects that a Layer parameter does not exist within the collection.
MapException Generic Exception thrown by class methods within the com.esri.mo2.map.dpy package.
NotSelectableException Thrown by FeatureLayer if you attempt to select Features, when the FeatureLayer has been marked *not* Selectable.
 

Package com.esri.mo2.map.dpy Description

Support for major Map components. Layers are defined here, as well as a Display and DisplayManager.
